1 olive oil
1 packet jasmine rice
½ cucumber
1 orange
1 packet Peeled Prawns
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet cornflour
1 tbs plain flour
1 sachet sesame seeds
2 tsp soy sauce
2 tsp honey
1 packet Baby Leaves
drizzle vinegar (white  wine or rice wine)

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water.
• Add jasmine rice and a pinch of salt and cook, uncovered, over a high heat until tender, 12-14 minutes.
• Drain, rinse with warm water and set aside.
• Slice cucumber into half-moons. Juice the orange.

• In a medium bowl, combine peeled prawns, sweet soy seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil.
• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with enough olive oil to cover the base. Meanwhile, to the bowl with the prawns, add cornflour and the plain flour and toss to combine.
• When oil is hot, dust off any excess flour from prawns, then cook, tossing occasionally, until pink and starting to curl up, 3-4 minutes.
• Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.

• Wipe out and return frying pan to medium heat. Toast sesame seeds, until golden, 1-2 minutes.
• Add orange juice and the soy sauce and honey and simmer until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes.
• In a medium bowl, combine cucumber, mixed salad leaves and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.

 • Divide jasmine rice between bowls.
• Top with prawns and pour over the orange sesame glaze.
• Serve with fresh cucumber salad. Enjoy!